In this scene, Chremes, by means of Crito, comes to know that Glycerium was his own daughter ; which immediately reconciles Simo to his son’s amour, and raises Pamphilus to the height os his wishes. It appears from what Crito says, as he is coming out of the house of Glycerium, that Pamphilus had been requesting him to do his utmost to convince the old men that she was really an Athenian.
